item.description: Our founding fathers established a respected and profound tradition of oratorical sesquipedalianism. Their intent was to direct the unwashed masses of the American public away from tyranny and hedonism, away from populism and Catholicism, away from Asians and Irish, and away from those diabolical Finnish. They wanted to direct the country towards moderate corporate tax structures and an immigration system geared towards Anglo-Saxon racial purity. These visionaries realized it could be as uncomplicated and straightforward as choosing the most intensely syllable laden words from the godforsaken depths of an 18th century philosopherâ€™s annotated thesaurus.
